ZAGREB, Croatia â The Croatian government on Monday (12 June) recognised Montenegro as an independent and sovereign state and offered to establish official diplomatic relations.
That makes Croatia the fourth country -- after Iceland, Switzerland and Russia -- and the first former Yugoslav republic to recognise Montenegro.
Russia formally recognised Montenegro on Sunday.
